

Your Display Card may offer high-resolution fonts, the ClearText fonts,
to improve the readability of text display.

To check whether your Display Card offers ClearText, please run DMODE
to see if there are ClearText options available for selection under MODE 2,
MODE 3, or MODE 22.

ClearText can be activated via DMODE menu or DMODE command syntax.
Please type DMODE COMMAND? for information on DMODE command syntax.
Upon activating the ClearText, DMODE will create CT_FONT.FNT on Drive C:
